What you need to know:

The Argentine was hired as the man to win the Champions League for the Qatar-owned club after predecessor Thomas Tuchel took them to last season's final only to lose to Bayern MunichTheir form in Ligue 1 has sometimes been poor given PSG's resources, which go beyond the simple fact of possessing the two most expensive players in the world in Neymar and Kylian MbappePSG have been devastating away from home, where they can best harvest the searing pace of Mbappe on the break